description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Changing Minds IAPT was established in 2008 and has developed into a successful and innovative service providing psychological therapies for people across Northamptonshire. The service is looking to recruit a qualified High Intensity Therapist to provide CBT to people with moderate to severe depression and anxiety disorders. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will work directly with patients using CBT interventions as part of a expanding IAPT team. Currently this will involve working remotely using telephone and digital channels. Y&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ou will be enthusiastic, hard-working and have the capability to meet specified targets. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are also interested in therapists who are dual trained in EMDR. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to providing training, development, high quality supervision and support to all our staff. We are a friendly, supportive team with a focus on promoting both the wellbeing of staff and patients.&lt;/p&gt;
